article.description: Prairie View A&M edges Alcorn State 83-80 in SWAC finale
article.headline: Prairie View A&M edges Alcorn State 83-80 in SWAC finale
article.linkText: Prairie View A&M edges Alcorn State 83-80 in SWAC finale
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas -- Montrael Scott poured in 31 points and Tre Hagood added 20 -- including a pair of free throws with 10 seconds left -- as Prairie View A&M closed out the regular season with an 83-80 win over Alcorn State on Saturday night. Scott hit 9 of 16 shots, including 5 3-pointers, and was a perfect 8 of 8 from the foul line to score his career-high 31. Prairie View (14-17, 12-6 SWAC), which has won eight of nine, closed out the regular season as the No. 4 seed to the SWAC tournament in Houston. Alcorn State (5-25, 4-14) was led by LeAntwan Luckett's 20 points and 18 from Reginald Johnson. The Braves sliced a 12-point Prairie View lead to 81-80 when Tamarico Wilson stole the ball from Hagood -- his only steal of the game -- and scored a layup with 42 seconds left. Wilson finished with 14 points.
